# The Erdtree · the golden tree at the center of the world

The Erdtree is the colossal tree of gold that dominates the Lands Between, visible from everywhere. It is the seat of the Golden Order, the refined form of the primordial Crucible, the home of the Elden Ring, and Marika's prison. Wherever a traveler stands in the Lands Between, the golden tree stands on the horizon — the landmark by which the whole world orients itself.

Its blessing is grace. Its leaves are said to return the dead to its roots in cycles of burial, the world's dead folding back into the tree that crowns it. In this way the Erdtree is not only a monument but a covenant: faith, law, and landmark in one, the axis around which the Lands Between turn.

Yet the tree is sealed by thorns. It cannot be entered — not until it is made to burn with the Fell God's flame. The world's center is also the world's lock, and only fire opens it.

Its emergence is spiritual because the Erdtree is the soul of the golden Order made visible: godhood housed, grace dispensed, faith given a body of gold at the center of the world.
